And, Class of 2016, you are graduating at such an inflection point. \'a0Since the start of this new millennium, you\'92ve already witnessed horrific terrorist attacks, and war, and a Great Recession. \'a0You\'92ve seen economic and technological and cultural shifts that are profoundly altering how we work and how we communicate, how we live, how we form families. \'a0The pace of change is not subsiding; it is accelerating. \'a0And these changes offer not only great opportunity, but also great peril.\'a0\
