So you\'92ve got the tools to lead us. \'a0And precisely because I have so much confidence in you, I\'92m not going to spend the remainder of my time telling you exactly how you\'92re going to make the world better. \'a0You\'92ll figure it out. \'a0You\'92ll look at things with fresher eyes, unencumbered by the biases and blind spots and inertia and general crankiness of your parents and grandparents and old heads like me. \'a0But I do have a couple of suggestions that you may find useful as you go out there and conquer the world.\'a0\
Point number one: \'a0When you hear someone longing for the \'93good old days,\'94 take it with a grain of salt. \'a0(Laughter and applause.) \'a0Take it with a grain of salt. \'a0We live in a great nation and we are rightly proud of our history. \'a0We are beneficiaries of the labor and the grit and the courage of generations who came before. \'a0But I guess it's part of human nature, especially in times of change and uncertainty, to want to look backwards and long for some imaginary past when everything worked, and the economy hummed, and all politicians were wise, and every kid was well-mannered, and America pretty much did whatever it wanted around the world. \'a0\
