Meanwhile, in the eight years since most of you started high school, we\'92re also better off. \'a0You and your fellow graduates are entering the job market with better prospects than any time since 2007. \'a0Twenty million more Americans know the financial security of health insurance. \'a0We\'92re less dependent on foreign oil. \'a0We\'92ve doubled the production of clean energy. \'a0We have cut the high school dropout rate. \'a0We've cut the deficit by two-thirds. \'a0Marriage equality is the law of the land. \'a0(Applause.) \'a0 \'a0\
