And if participation means voting, and it means compromise, and organizing and advocacy, it also means listening to those who don\'92t agree with you. \'a0I know a couple years ago, folks on this campus got upset that Condoleezza Rice was supposed to speak at a commencement. \'a0Now, I don't think it's a secret that I disagree with many of the foreign policies of Dr. Rice and the previous administration. \'a0But the notion that this community or the country would be better served by not hearing from a former Secretary of State, or shutting out what she had to say -- I believe that\'92s misguided. \'a0(Applause.) \'a0I don't think that's how democracy works best, when we're not even willing to listen to each other. \'a0(Applause.) \'a0I believe that's misguided. \'a0\
If you disagree with somebody, bring them in -- (applause)\'a0-- and ask them tough questions. \'a0Hold their feet to the fire. \'a0Make them defend their positions. \'a0(Applause.) \'a0If somebody has got a bad or offensive idea, prove it wrong. \'a0Engage it. \'a0Debate it. \'a0Stand up for what you believe in. \'a0(Applause.) \'a0Don't be scared to take somebody on. \'a0Don't feel like you got to shut your ears off because you're too fragile and somebody might offend your sensibilities. \'a0Go at them if they\'92re not making any sense. Use your logic and reason and words. \'a0And by doing so, you\'92ll strengthen your own position, and you\'92ll hone your arguments. \'a0And maybe you\'92ll learn something and realize you don't know everything. \'a0And you may have a new understanding not only about what your opponents believe but maybe what you believe. \'a0Either way, you win. \'a0And more importantly, our democracy wins. \'a0(Applause.) \'a0\
So, anyway, all right. \'a0That's it, Class of 2016 -- (laughter) -- a few suggestions on how you can change the world. Except maybe I've got one last suggestion. \'a0(Applause.) \'a0Just one. \'a0And that is, gear yourself for the long haul. \'a0Whatever path you choose -- business, nonprofits, government, education, health care, the arts -- whatever it is, you're going to have some setbacks. \'a0You will deal occasionally with foolish people. \'a0You will be frustrated. \'a0You\'92ll have a boss that's not great. \'a0You won\'92t always get everything you want -- at least not as fast as you want it. \'a0So you have to stick with it. \'a0You have to be persistent. \'a0And success, however small, however incomplete, success is still success. \'a0I always tell my daughters, you know, better is good. \'a0It may not be perfect, it may not be great, but it's good. \'a0That's how progress happens -- in societies and in our own lives. \'a0\
